<hr>
<h2><strong>5 Steps To<br>
Handwashing</strong></h2>
<hr>
<ol>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<strong>Wet</strong> your hands with clean, running water (warm or cold), turn off the tap, and apply soap.</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<strong>Lather</strong> your hands by rubbing them together with the soap. Lather the backs of your hands, between your fingers, and under your nails.</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<strong>Scrub</strong> your hands for at least 20 seconds. Need a timer? Hum the “Happy Birthday” song from beginning to end TWICE.</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<strong>Rinse</strong> your hands well under clean, running water.</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<strong>Dry</strong> your hands using a clean towel or air dry them.</li>
</ol>
<p><a href="https://youtu.be/d914EnpU4Fo" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-5086 size-medium" src="https://www.swschools.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-03-at-4.08.57-PM-300x165.png" alt="SWS Handwashing" width="300" height="165" srcset="https://www.swschools.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-03-at-4.08.57-PM-300x165.png 300w, https://www.swschools.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-03-at-4.08.57-PM.png 575w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></a></p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Take Steps To Protect Others</strong></h2>
<hr>
<ol>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Stay home if you are sick</strong></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Cover coughs and sneezes</strong></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Wear a facemark if you are sick</strong></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Clean and disinfect frequently touched surfaces daily.</strong></li>
</ol>
<p><a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/prevention.html" target="_blank">Learn More &gt;</a></p>
